agues. It is initially thought that the man who struck her was drunk behind the wheel, but Dr. Sharpe learns that he suffered a stroke and is ill. Dr. Reynolds performs the officer's surgery, but she doesn't make it. The officers decide to donate money their fallen comrade would've received to help pay for his treatment so he can recover. Dr. Kapoor and Dr. Frome work with a deaf patient who just received a cochlear implant. And Dr. Frome faces the fact that Jemma no longer needs him.\n |LineColor       = AFF7FB\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 20\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 20\n |Title           = Preventable\n |DirectedBy      = [[Thomas Carter (director)|Thomas Carter]]\n |WrittenBy       = Aaron Ginsburg\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|4|30}}\n |Viewers         = 5.24<ref name=\"1.20\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/fbi-masterchef-junior-adjust-up-bless-this-mess-adjusts-down-tuesday-final-ratings/|title='FBI,' 'MasterChef Junior' adjust up, 'Bless This Mess' adjusts down: Tuesday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=TV by the Numbers|date=May 1, 2019|accessdate=May 1, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501214754/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/fbi-masterchef-junior-adjust-up-bless-this-mess-adjusts-down-tuesday-final-ratings/|archive-date=May 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = {{Plot|episode|date=December 2019}}Max wakes up miserable and realizes his hair has started to fall out, he goes in to work with a knit beanie to cover his head and starts having mood swings. Dr. Reynolds leads a morbidity and mortality (M&M) conference about the police officer that died in the previous episode. Max pushes the M&M conference too far and ends up insulting Dr. Reynolds in front of his colleagues and staff and a rift develops between the two. Dr. Sharpe sees Max's mood has changed and talks to Dr. Stauton and learns that Max's cancer is not responding to the chemo or radiation. Dr. R