ks of Dr. Kapoor treating a patient who has been in a coma for several years. \n |LineColor       = 91D27D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 35\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n |Title           = In the Graveyard\n |DirectedBy      = [[Darnell Martin]]\n |WrittenBy       = Josh Carlebach\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|11}}\n |Viewers         = 4.47<ref name=\"2.13\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-11-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.11.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=February 12, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=February 12, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Max is told he needs to cut $2 million from the budget. \n |LineColor       = 91D27D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 36\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 14\n |Title           = Sabbath\n |DirectedBy      = [[Ryan Eggold]]\n |WrittenBy       = {{storyTeleplay|tfirst=1|t=David Schulner|s=Marc Gaffen & David Schulner}}\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|18}}\n |Viewers         = 4.71<ref name=\"2.14\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-18-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.18.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=February 20, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = A woman comes in after hitting her head and her mysterious disease moves at a rapid speed. \n |LineColor       = 91D27D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 37\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 15\n |Title           = Double Blind\n |DirectedBy      = [[Allison Liddi-Brown]]\n |WrittenBy       = Shaun Cassidy\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|25}}\n |Viewers         = 5.16<ref name=\"2.15\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-25-2020.html|