d is inadvertently trapped, in an elevator with a young man who is bleeding out. Max looks for an alternative to crowdfunding as he believes it is unfair. Dr. Sharpe prepares for a \u201cFight Cancer\u201d charity event and discovers how the young cancer survivors feel. In the end, everyone bids a fond farewell to Dr. Reynolds as he leaves New Amsterdam for San Francisco.\n |LineColor       = 91D27D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 40\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 18\n |Title           = Matter of Seconds\n |DirectedBy      = Dinh Thai\n |WrittenBy       = Aaron Ginsburg\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|14}}\n |Viewers         = 6.03<ref name=\"2.18\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-14-2020.html|title=ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals\u00a0& Network Finals: 4.14.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=April 15, 2020|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = \n----\nThis episode opens with a message from actors Ryan Eggold and Daniel Dae Kim, explaining how \"Matter of Seconds\" replaced the scheduled episode \"Pandemic\" because its events were close to the actual [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]. Scenes featuring Kim's character Dr. Cassian Shin from \"Pandemic\" were shown to introduce viewers to the character ahead of his appearance in this episode.\n |LineColor       = 91D27D\n}}\n}}\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nOn September 25, 2017, [[NBC]] announced that it had given the production, then titled ''Bellevue'', a [[put pilot]] commitment. The pilot was written by [[David Schulner]], who was also set to executive produce alongside [[Peter Horton]]. Eric Manheimer, the former medical director at New York City's [[Bellevue Hospital]], was expected to serve as a producer. [[Universal Television]] was the production company involved with the pilot.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=NBC Nabs \u2018Bellevue\u2019 Medical Drama From David Schulner & Peter Horton As Put Pilot|url=https://deadline.com/2017/09/bellevue-medical-drama-david-schulner-peter-horton-nbc-put-pilot-1202176613/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=May 5, 2018|date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180505134932/http://deadline.com/2017/09/bellevue-medical-drama-david-schulner-peter-horton-nbc-put-pilot-1202176613/|archive-date=May 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn January 12, 2018, it was reported that NBC had given the production an official pilot order. It was further reported that Horton was expected to direct the pilot episode.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=NBC Orders Bellevue Medical Drama Pilot From David Schulner & Peter Horton|url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/nbc-orders-bellevue-medical-drama-pilot-from-david-schulner-peter-horton-1202242302/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 5, 2018|date=January 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180505135433/http://deadline.com/2018/01/nbc-orders-bellevue-medical-drama-pilot-from-david-schulner-peter-horton-1202242302/|archive-date=May 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On May 4, 2018, it was announced that NBC had given the production a series order. It was also reported that Pico Creek Productions and Mount Moriah Productions would serve as additional production companies.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\">{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=NBC Picks Up Medical Drama \u2018New Amsterdam\u2019 To Series; What Does That Mean For \u2018Chicago Med\u2019?|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/nbc-medical-drama-new-amsterdam-series-chicago-med-renewal-ryan-eggold-1202383231/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 4, 2018|date=May 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180505034602/http://deadline.com/2018/05/nbc-medical-drama-new-amsterdam-series-chicago-med-renewal-ryan-eggold-1202383231/|archive-date=May 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Otterson|first1=Joe|title=Medical Drama \u2018New Amsterdam\u2019 Lands Series Order at NBC|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/new-amsterdam-series-order-nbc-1202800204/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=May 4, 2018|date=May 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180505035147/http://variety.com/2018/tv/news/new-amsterdam-series-order-nbc-1202800204/|archive-date=May 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Goldberg|first1=Lesley|title=Medical Drama 'New Amsterdam' Ordered to Series at NBC|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/medical-drama-new-amsterdam-ordered-series-at-nbc-1108878|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=May 4, 2018|date=May 4, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180505052743/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/medical-drama-new-amsterdam-ordered-series-at-nbc-1108878|archive-date=May 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On October 10, 2018, it was announced that NBC had ordered an additional nine episodes of the series, bringing the first season total up to twenty-two episodes.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Andreeva |first1=Nellie |title=\u2018New Amsterdam\u2019 Gets Back 9 Order At NBC |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/new-amsterdam-back-9-order-from-nbc-full-season-1-1202480187/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=October 10, 2018 |date=October 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181010202537/https://deadline.com/2018/10/new-amsterdam-back-9-order-from-nbc-full-season-1-1202480187/ |archive-date=October 10, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> On February 4, 2019, it was announced during the [[Television Critics Association]]'s annual winter press tour that the series had been renewed for a second season.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |title=\u2018New Amsterdam\u2019 Renewed For Season 2 By NBC |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/new-amsterdam-renewed-season-2-nbc-1202549227/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=February 4, 2019 |date=February 4, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190205131520/https://deadline.com/2019/02/new-amsterdam-renewed-season-2-nbc-1202549227/ |archive-date=February 5, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> In January 2020, NBC renewed ''New Amsterdam'' for a third, fourth, and fifth season.<ref name=\"Jan2020Renewal\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/new-amsterdam-renewed-3-more-seasons-nbc-through-2022-23-tca-1202827534/|title=\u2018New Amsterdam\u2019 Renewed For 3 More Seasons By NBC Through 2022-23 \u2013 TCA|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=January 11, 2020|accessdate=January 11, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200111180141/https://deadline.com/2020/01/new-amsterdam-renewed-3-more-seasons-nbc-through-2022-23-tca-1202827534/|archive-date=January 11, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn February 2018, it was announced that [[Freema Agyeman]], [[Anupam Kher]], [[Janet Montgomery]], and [[Tyler Labine]] had been cast in lead roles in the pilot.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Petski|first1=Denise|title=Freema Agyeman & Anupam Kher Cast In NBC\u2019s Bellevue Medical Drama Pilot|url=https://deadline.com/2018/02/freema-agyeman-anupam-kher-cast-in-nbc-medical-drama-pilot-1202281820/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 4, 2018|date=February 8, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180505135132/http://deadline.com/2018/02/freema-agyeman-anupam-kher-cast-in-nbc-medical-drama-pilot-1202281820/|archive-date=May 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=Janet Montgomery To Star In NBC\u2019s Bellevue Medical Drama Pilot|url=https://deadline.com/2018/02/janet-montgomery-cast-nbc-bellevue-medical-drama-pilot-david-schulner-peter-horton-1202290360/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 4, 2018|date=February 15, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180505134934/http://deadline.com/2018/02/janet-montgomery-cast-nbc-bellevue-medical-drama-pilot-david-schulner-peter-horton-1202290360/|archive-date=May 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|title=Tyler Labine To Co-Star In NBC\u2019s Bellevue Medical Drama Pilot|url=https://deadline.com/2018/02/tyler-labine-cast-nbc-bellevue-medical-drama-pilot-1202297839/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 4, 2018|date=February 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180505135020/http://deadline.com/2018/02/tyler-labine-cast-nbc-bellevue-medical-drama-pilot-1202297839/|archive-date=May 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2018, it was reported that [[Ryan Eggold]] and [[Jocko Sims]] had also joined the main cast.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|title=Ryan Eggold To Topline NBC\u2019s David Schulner/Peter Horton Medical Drama Pilot|url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/ryan-eggold-star-nbc-david-schulner-peter-horton-medical-drama-pilot-1202311635/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 4, 2018|date=March 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180505134915/http://deadline.com/2018/03/ryan-eggold-star-nbc-david-schulner-peter-horton-medical-drama-pilot-1202311635/|archive-date=May 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|title=\u2018The Last Ship\u2019s Jocko Sims To Co-Star In NBC\u2019s David Schulner Medical Drama Pilot|url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/jocko-sims-cast-nbc-bellevue-david-schulner-medical-drama-pilot-the-last-ship-season-6-1202336180/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 4, 2018|date=March 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180505135039/http://deadline.com/2018/03/jocko-sims-cast-nbc-bellevue-david-schulner-medical-drama-pilot-the-last-ship-season-6-1202336180/|archive-date=May 5, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On September 26, 2018, it was announced that [[Margot Bingham]] had joined the cast in a recurring role.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |title=\u2018New Amsterdam\u2019: Margot Bingham To Recur On NBC Medical Drama |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/new-amsterdam-margot-bingham-recur-nbc-medical-drama-1202471983/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=September 27, 2018 |date=September 27, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180927050410/https://deadline.com/2018/09/new-amsterdam-margot-bingham-recur-nbc-medical-drama-1202471983/ |archive-date=September 27, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> On November 6, 2018, it was reported that [[Sendhil Ramamurthy]] had been cast in a recurring role.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Andreeva |first1=Nellie |title=Sendhil Ramamurthy Joins NBC's 'New Amsterdam' In Recurring Role |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/sendhil-ramamurthy-cast-new-amsterdam-recurring-role-nbc-1202496881/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=November 6, 2018 |date=November 6, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106214910/https://deadline.com/2018/11/sendhil-ramamurthy-cast-new-amsterdam-recurring-role-nbc-1202496881/ |archive-date=November 6, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nFilming for the series takes place at New York City area hospitals including Bellevue Hospital and its surrounding area, [[Metropolitan Hospital Center]], [[Woodhull Hospital]], and [[Kings County Hospital Center]]. By October 2018, Universal Television had paid [[NYC Health + Hospitals]], the corporation that oversees New York City's public hospitals, {{USD|665,000}} to film in the hospitals. Robert de Luna, a spokesman for Health + Hospitals, said certain areas that are \"unoccupied and unstaffed... presents a great opportunity for a production company and a welcome source of revenue for our health system.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2018/10/27/new-amsterdam-filming-pumps-money-into-citys-hospitals/|title=\u2018New Amsterdam\u2019 filming pumps money into city\u2019s hospitals|last=Klein|first=Melissa|work=[[New York Post]]|date=October 27, 2018|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 12, 2020, production of ''New Amsterdam'' and other Universal Television series was halted due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/coronavirus-nbcuniversal-halts-production-35-series-chicagofire-chicago-pd-chicago-med-fbi-law-order-svu-kelly-clarkson-show-angelyne-1202881992/|title=Coronavirus: NBCUniversal Halts Production On About 35 Series Including \u2018Chicago\u2019 Dramas, \u2018Kelly Clarkson Show\u2019 & \u2018Angelyne\u2019|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 12, 2020|access-date=March 14, 2020}}</ref> A supply of [[personal protective equipment]] used by the series was donated to the [[New York State Department of Health]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/new-amsterdam-showrunner-david-schulner-helping-new-york-relief-efforts-medical-supplies-coronavirus-1202888357/|title=Coronavirus: \u2018New Amsterdam\u2019 EP David Schulner On Helping New York Relief Efforts With Medical Supplies|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n''New Amsterdam'' premiered on NBC on September 25, 2018 at 10 p.m.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |title=NBC Sets Fall 2018 Premiere Dates: \u2018This Is Us\u2019, \u2018The Voice\u2019, \u2018Manifest\u2019 & More |url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/nbc-fall-2018-premiere-dates-this-is-us-the-voice-manifest-chicago-1202413520/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=June 19, 2018 |date=June 19, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620001152/https://deadline.com/2018/06/nbc-fall-2018-premiere-dates-this-is-us-the-voice-manifest-chicago-1202413520/ |archive-date=June 20, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The second season premiered on September 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/nbc-fall-premiere-dates-2019-the-voice-chicago-bluff-city-law-sunnyside-perfect-harmony-1202633630/|title=NBC Fall Premiere Dates: \u2018The Voice\u2019, \u2018This Is Us\u2019, New \u2018Bluff City Law\u2019 & \u2018Sunnyside\u2019, More|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Erik|last=Pederson|date=June 17, 2019|accessdate=June 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190617180916/https://deadline.com/2019/06/nbc-fall-premiere-dates-2019-the-voice-chicago-bluff-city-law-sunnyside-perfect-harmony-1202633630/|archive-date=June 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\nThe second season's eighteenth episode, \"Our Doors Are Always Open\" (originally titled \"Pandemic\"), that was scheduled to air on April 7, 2020,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20200323nbc12/|title=(#218) \"OUR DOORS ARE ALWAYS OPEN\"|publisher=The Futon Critic|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"218Pulled\" /> was postponed by NBC, as its subject matter (dealing with a flu pandemic in New York City) was considered sensitive due to the severity of [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in New York (state)|the COVID-19 pandemic in New York state]]. Schulner felt that \"the world needs a lot less fiction right now, and a lot more facts\". The final episode completed before the suspension of production would be designated as the season finale, and aired on April 14.<ref name=\"218Pulled\">{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/new-amsterdam-flu-pandemic-episode-shelved-pulled-nbc-season-2-finale-date-creator-david-schulner-essay-explains-ryan-eggold-daniel-dae-kim-1202892215/|title=\u2018New Amsterdam\u2019 Flu Pandemic Episode Shelved By NBC: \u201cThe World Needs A Lot Less Fiction Right Now, And A Lot More Facts,\u201d Creator David Schulner Says|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=March 25, 2020|website=Deadline|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Marketing===\nOn May 13, 2018, [[NBC]] released the first official trailer for the series.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Petski|first1=Denise|title=NBC New Series Trailers: 'Manifest', 'New Amsterdam', 'I Feel Bad'|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/nbc-new-series-trailers-fall-2018-lineup-manifest-new-amsterdam-i-feel-bad-1202389768/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 13, 2018|date=May 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180513200736/http://deadline.com/2018/05/nbc-new-series-trailers-fall-2018-lineup-manifest-new-amsterdam-i-feel-bad-1202389768/|archive-date=May 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> On June 22, 2018, a screening of the series was held during Seriesfest, an annual international television festival, at the [[Denver Art Museum]]'s Lewis I. Sharp Auditorium in [[Denver|Denver, Colorado]]. The screening was followed by a question-and-answer session with series lead [[Ryan Eggold]] and executive producers [[David Schulner]] and [[Peter Horton]]. It was moderated by ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]''{{'}}s executive West Coast editor, Krista Smith.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ramos |first1=Dino-Ray |title=SeriesFest Unveils Initial Lineup, Sets World Premiere Of NBC Drama 'New Amsterdam' |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/seriesfest-lineup-new-amsterdam-premiere-events-panels-1202400477/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=May 31, 2018 |date=May 30, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180605005705/https://deadline.com/2018/05/seriesfest-lineup-new-amsterdam-premiere-events-panels-1202400477/ |archive-date=June 5, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> On September 10, 2018, the series took part in the 12th Annual PaleyFest Fall Television Previews which featured a preview screening of the series.<ref>{{cite web |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |title=PaleyFest Fall TV Previews Sets Initial Lineup: Tim Allen, Sarah Silverman, Aaron Paul & More |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/paleyfest-fall-tv-previews-tim-allen-sarah-silverman-aaron-paul-nathan-fillion-hulu-netflix-abc-cbs-1202432095/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=July 29, 2018 |date=July 24, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180728131322/https://deadline.com/2018/07/paleyfest-fall-tv-previews-tim-allen-sarah-silverman-aaron-paul-nathan-fillion-hulu-netflix-abc-cbs-1202432095/ |archive-date=July 28, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Distribution===\nIn the United Kingdom, the series premiered its first half of Season 1 on Amazon Video on February 8, 2019. Amazon Video releases the series in binge-ready batches, with further episodes released in May 2019 and November 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last=White |first1=Peter |title=Amazon Prime Video Picks Up UK Rights To NBC Medical Drama \u2018New Amsterdam\u2019; Sets February Premiere |url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/amazon-new-amsterdam-uk-1202532649/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=January 10, 2019 |date=January 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190110134656/https://deadline.com/2019/01/amazon-new-amsterdam-uk-1202532649/ |archive-date=January 10, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nThe series has been met with a mixed to negative response from critics upon its premiere. On the review aggregation website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series holds a 31% approval rating with an average rating of 5.74 out of 10 based on 29 reviews. The website's critical consensus reads, \"Overcrowded, overwrought, and overly familiar, ''New Amsterdam'' plays more like an exquisite corpse of pre-existing shows than a breakthrough for the genre&nbsp;\u2013 though that may be enough for medical drama devotees.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/new_amsterdam_2018/s01|title=New Amsterdam: Season 1|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media|Fandango]]|accessdate=January 5, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190109031144/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/new_amsterdam_2018/s01|archive-date=January 9, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Metacritic]], which uses a weighted average, assigned the series a score of 47 out of 100 based on 14 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/new-amsterdam-2018|title