w\u00f3w (ice hockey)|Czarni Lw\u00f3w]]\n| 1935\n|-\n! 1 \n| [[D\u0105b Katowice]]\n| 1939\n|-\n! 1 \n| [[KTH Krynica]]\n| 1950\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}<!--added above External links/Sources by script-assisted edit-->\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.hokej.net/ Hokej.Net]\n* [http://polskihokej.eu/ The Polish Ice Hockey Federation's website]\n* [http://polskahokejliga.pl/ PHL Statistics]\n\n{{Ice Hockey Leagues}}\n{{Ice hockey in Poland}}\n{{Polska Liga Hokejowa seasons}}\n\n[[Category:Polska Hokej Liga| ]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey leagues in Europe]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey leagues in Poland|1]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Sports league\n| title = Ekstraklasa\n| current_season =\n| logo =\n| pixels = 200px\n| caption =\n| formerly = I Liga<br/>Polska Liga Hokejowa\n| sport = Ice hockey\n| founded = 1926 (Original)<br/>1955 (I Liga)\n| fame = \n| motto =\n| inaugural = [[1955\u201356 Polska Liga Hokejowa season|1955\u201356]]\n| teams = \n| country = [[Poland]]\n| champion =\n| most_champs = [[Podhale Nowy Targ]] (19)\n| qualification = \n| folded = \n| website = [http://www.hokej.net/ hokej.net]\n| ceo = \n| TV = \n| related_comps = [[Polish Cup (ice hockey)|Polish Cup]]<br/>[[Polish 1. Liga]]\n| founder = [[Polish Ice Hockey Federation]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Polish ice hockey Ekstraklasa''' ({{lang-pl|Ekstraliga polska w hokeju na lodzie}}) was the premier [[ice hockey]] league in [[Poland]]. Previously, it was known as the '''I Liga''' or '''Ekstraklasa''' from 1926\u20131999, and the '''Polska Liga Hokejowa''' from 1999\u20132013. In 2013, it was reorganized as a [[Limited liability company#Poland|limited liability company]] and renamed the '''[[Polska Hokej Liga]]'''.\n\n== History ==\nThe championship started in 1925-26. At first it was a non-league system composed of regional tournaments. The tournaments had two stages. The best teams qualified to the final tournament, of which the winner was declared champion. In 1938, the Polish Ice Hockey Federation decided to reorganise the championship, by creating a league system. Those plans were abandoned due to outbreak of [[World War II]].\n\nThe current structure of the league began in 1955.\n\nThe 2019-20 season was suspended on March 11th, 2020 due to health concerns with the spreading coronavirus. GKS Tychy was named league champions and will represent the league in the Champions Hockey Leauge, Re-Plast Unia O\u015bwi\u0119cim was named the runner ups and earned a spot in the Continental Cup, third-place was shared by JKH GKS Jastrz\u0119bie and GKS Katowice \n\n== Medalists ==\n{| border=1 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 style=\"border: 1px gray solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%\"\n|- bgcolor=#ececec\n!Year  \t \n!1st place  \t \n!2nd place  \t \n!3rd place\n|-\n|'''1925-26''' \t\n|\t\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''1926-27''' \t\n|[[AZS Warszawa]] \t\n|[[Warszawskie Towarzystwo \u0141y\u017cwiarskie|WT\u0141 Warszawa]] \t\n|[[Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w (ice hockey)|Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w]]\n|-\n|'''1927-28''' \t\n|[[AZS Warszawa]] \t\n|[[Legia Warszawa (ice hockey)|Legia Warszawa]] \t\n|[[TKH Toru\u0144|TKS Toru\u0144]]\n|-\n|'''1928-29'''\t\n|[[AZS Warszawa]] \t\n|[[Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w (ice hockey)|Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w]] \t\n|[[Legia Warszawa (ice hockey)|Legia Warszawa]]\n|-\n|'''1929-30''' \t\n|[[AZS Warszawa]] \t\n|[[Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w (ice hockey)|Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w]] \t\n|[[Legia Warszawa (ice hockey)|Legia Warszawa]]\n|-\n|'''1930-31'''\t\n|[[AZS Warszawa]] \t\n|[[Legia Warszawa (ice hockey)|Legia Warszawa]] \t\n|[[AZS Pozna\u0144 (ice hockey)|AZS Pozna\u0144]]\n|-\n|1931-32\t\n|<ref>No championship due to [[Poland men's national ice hockey team|national team]] preparation for the [[Ice hockey at the 1932 Winter Olympics|Winter Olympics]]</ref>\n|\n|\n|-\n|'''1932-33'''\t\n|[[Legia Warszawa (ice hockey)|Legia Warszawa]] & [[Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w (ice hockey)|Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w]] \n|\t \n|[[AZS Pozna\u0144 (ice hockey)|AZS Pozna\u0144]]\n|-\n|'''1933-34'''\t\n|[[AZ